<subSubSection id="C3196578FF90FFC25CB1FC598F1F0CDF" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="115" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BBC36F3FF90FFC25CB1FC598F1F0CDF" blockId="1.[174,1233,762,1033]" lastBlockId="2.[166,1225,175,314]" lastPageId="2" lastPageNumber="115" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">
D i a g n o s i s. This species can be recognized from having wing with large brown apical fleck (
<figureCitation id="13382A76FF90FFC15D4DFC648F220833" box="[287,348,1006,1033]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="1.[169,202,1730,1752]" captionTargetBox="[238,1170,1057,1702]" captionTargetId="figure-370@1.[225,1170,1057,1716]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Fig. 1. Allopiophila luteata (1–2) and Mycetaulus bipunctatus (3–4): 1, 3 — habitus, left; 2 — head and mesonotum, dorsal; habitus, dorsal and right. Рис. 1. Allopiophila luteata (1–2) и Mycetaulus bipunctatus (3–4): 1, 3 — общий вид, слева; 2 — голова и среднеспинка, сверху; 4 — общий вид, справа и сверху." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6412917" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6412917/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">fig. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<emphasis id="B977EAE1FF90FFC15D39FC648F070832" box="[363,377,1006,1032]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">4</emphasis>
) with brownish yellow mesonotum and black abdomen (
<figureCitation id="13382A76FF90FFC1587AFC648A1B0833" box="[1064,1125,1006,1033]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="1.[169,202,1730,1752]" captionTargetBox="[238,1170,1057,1702]" captionTargetId="figure-370@1.[225,1170,1057,1716]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="Fig. 1. Allopiophila luteata (1–2) and Mycetaulus bipunctatus (3–4): 1, 3 — habitus, left; 2 — head and mesonotum, dorsal; habitus, dorsal and right. Рис. 1. Allopiophila luteata (1–2) и Mycetaulus bipunctatus (3–4): 1, 3 — общий вид, слева; 2 — голова и среднеспинка, сверху; 4 — общий вид, справа и сверху." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6412917" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6412917/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">fig. 1</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13382A76FF90FFC15826FC648AFC0832" box="[1140,1154,1006,1032]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="3.[174,207,1736,1758]" captionTargetBox="[240,1131,825,1695]" captionTargetId="figure-293@3.[240,1134,811,1710]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig. 3. Prochyliza nigrimana (1), Protopiophila latipes (2), Stearibia nigriceps (3–4), and Neottiophilum praeustum (5): 1, 3 — habitus, left; 2, 4 — head and mesonotum, dorsal, 5 — wing. Рис. 3. Prochyliza nigrimana (1), Protopiophila latipes (2), Stearibia nigriceps (3–4) и Neottiophilum praeustum (5): 1, 3 — общий вид, слева; 2, 4 — голова и среднеспинка, сверху; 5 — крыло." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6412923" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6412923/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">
<emphasis id="B977EAE1FF90FFC15826FC648AFC0832" box="[1140,1154,1006,1032]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="114">3</emphasis>
</figureCitation>
), with strong orbital, well developed postpronotal and presutural supra-alar, and two pairs of katepisternal setae.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<caption id="DF7C667BFF90FFC15CFBF9488CA20B02" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6412917" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6412917" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6412917/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="114" startId="1.[169,202,1730,1752]" targetBox="[238,1170,1057,1702]" targetPageId="1">
